  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed at the campaign level and is discussed extensively in the validation narrative; however, not all individual ValidationResult records carry explicit hasUncertaintyQuantification links — the aleatory uncertainty characterization is described in prose rather than attached as structured artifacts to each result. This package contains the targeted W-AL-01 weakness: approximately half of the ValidationResult objects lack the hasUncertaintyQuantification field.",
