    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepts the CFD hemolysis model for the VAD COU subject to documented limitations. Achieved credibility levels fall below required levels for six of thirteen factors, consistent with the Low assurance designation. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed at the campaign level and is described in the validation narrative; the team notes that aleatory uncertainty from biological variability is characterized in prose across multiple validation reports and is considered sufficient for the current regulatory submission context. The team acknowledges that structured UQ artifacts are not linked to all individual ValidationResult records but judges that the campaign-level Monte Carlo documentation adequately covers the aleatory uncertainty space. Decision: Accepted with conditions — applicant must provide structured per-result UQ linkage prior to PMA submission.",
